&gt;&gt; We have time for
a few questions.

00:41:56.910 --> 00:41:58.390
There's mics on both
sides [inaudible],

00:41:58.390 --> 00:42:01.540
and Dan will call on you.

00:42:01.540 --> 00:42:03.890
&gt;&gt; Daniel Else: Or I
might not call on you.

00:42:05.100 --> 00:42:08.000
[Inaudible] There he is.

00:42:08.000 --> 00:42:10.300
&gt;&gt; Superb as --

00:42:16.530 --> 00:42:23.220
Is it on? I wondered whether, in
terms of why it was effective.

00:42:23.220 --> 00:42:25.460
Now, I'm making this
up as we go.

00:42:25.460 --> 00:42:28.160
You know from ten years
since I've had the pleasure

00:42:28.160 --> 00:42:29.560
of doing business with you.

00:42:29.560 --> 00:42:32.420
I wonder if there was a
coincidence between the state

00:42:32.420 --> 00:42:37.050
of military art and the state
of the physical sciences

00:42:37.050 --> 00:42:40.210
so that the physical science --
where the physical sciences were

00:42:40.210 --> 00:42:43.830
about to go that nicely
just happened to mesh.

00:42:43.830 --> 00:42:45.850
What I'm thinking of is,

00:42:45.850 --> 00:42:49.370
military power was largely
contained in very large,

00:42:49.370 --> 00:42:51.720
discrete objects that
were very lethal:

00:42:51.720 --> 00:42:53.970
submarines, bombers
and so forth.

00:42:53.970 --> 00:42:56.440
And if you happened
to come up with a way

00:42:56.440 --> 00:43:01.410
to detect small numbers of very
large -- hey, that's not bad.

00:43:01.410 --> 00:43:05.400
We're now at a point where
we're dealing with individuals

00:43:05.400 --> 00:43:08.470
and the state of physical
and social science

00:43:08.470 --> 00:43:11.370
and behavioral sciences,
not so clear

00:43:11.370 --> 00:43:13.050
at how much leverage
there is there.

00:43:13.050 --> 00:43:14.690
I mean, we tried
the, you know, the,

00:43:14.690 --> 00:43:17.790
what's the human terrain
teams and so forth and so on.

00:43:17.790 --> 00:43:21.170
But it doesn't seem to have
gained the kind of leverage

00:43:21.170 --> 00:43:24.860
that this process you've
described so well here did.

00:43:24.860 --> 00:43:26.580
And I wonder if there
was something I --

00:43:26.580 --> 00:43:29.090
again, I'm just making
this up as I go.

00:43:29.090 --> 00:43:32.540
But I wonder if it just happened
to be just the right point,

00:43:32.540 --> 00:43:36.150
both in the state of the
arts of war and the state

00:43:36.150 --> 00:43:37.940
of the physical sciences
that, by God,

00:43:37.940 --> 00:43:41.420
it meshed like hands in a glove.

00:43:43.190 --> 00:43:46.490
&gt;&gt; Daniel Else: Thank you for
that insightful question, Ben.

00:43:46.490 --> 00:43:50.190
I can only guess.

00:43:50.190 --> 00:43:51.650
And in hindsight,
everything looks

00:43:51.650 --> 00:43:53.350
like it really should've
worked out that way:

00:43:53.350 --> 00:43:55.950
boy, what a coincidence.

00:43:55.950 --> 00:43:58.020
I think, though, if
you take a look at it,

00:43:58.020 --> 00:44:01.320
the folks who were going through
it in 1949, 1945 didn't think

00:44:01.320 --> 00:44:02.970
that it was just a coincidence.

00:44:02.970 --> 00:44:05.660
They had to work very,
very hard and think outside

00:44:05.660 --> 00:44:08.310
of a whole number of boxes to
be able to come up with things

00:44:08.310 --> 00:44:13.120
like the VT fuse, the airborne
radar, submarine detection,

00:44:13.120 --> 00:44:16.590
etc., etc. Magnetic anomaly
detection was originated during

00:44:16.590 --> 00:44:17.890
this period.

00:44:17.890 --> 00:44:27.040
So I wonder -- I must defer the
question but pose another one.

00:44:27.040 --> 00:44:29.580
To what extent, I wonder,

00:44:32.730 --> 00:44:36.860
does the outside influence,
the outside status, let's say,

00:44:36.860 --> 00:44:40.870
of something like NDRC that
promotes independent thinking,

00:44:40.870 --> 00:44:45.230
how much did that play into
a specific number of devices?

00:44:45.230 --> 00:44:46.930
And I suspect there are
a significant number,

00:44:46.930 --> 00:44:49.680
but you'd have to do a whole
lot of research to figure out.

00:44:49.680 --> 00:44:52.310
Because the way that
the cooperation worked,

00:44:52.310 --> 00:44:54.670
perhaps some soldier in the
field would suggest something

00:44:54.670 --> 00:44:56.640
like a rocket-propelled grenade.

00:44:56.640 --> 00:44:59.340
Okay, well, NDRC would then
say, "Oh, that's a good idea,"

00:44:59.340 --> 00:45:02.030
jump on it, develop it,
hand it off to industry.

00:45:02.030 --> 00:45:03.730
Who gets credit for that?

00:45:03.730 --> 00:45:06.740
Because a lot of --
I'll give you an example

00:45:06.740 --> 00:45:09.170
of the atomic bomb.

00:45:09.170 --> 00:45:13.660
That was something that
in Vannevar Bush's view,

00:45:13.660 --> 00:45:15.080
was going to happen anyway.

00:45:15.080 --> 00:45:17.570
It didn't require a letter
from Albert Einstein to FDR.

00:45:17.570 --> 00:45:20.800
It didn't require anything
else, because as soon

00:45:20.800 --> 00:45:23.570
as nuclear fission, atomic
fission was discovered

00:45:23.570 --> 00:45:27.310
and proven in 1938, the
entire scientific community,

00:45:27.310 --> 00:45:30.250
whether it was funded by
governments or not, took off.

00:45:30.250 --> 00:45:31.870
They were looking to
see, is there a --

00:45:31.870 --> 00:45:35.080
is it feasible for there
to be atomic fission?

00:45:35.080 --> 00:45:37.790
And if so, then what
can we do with it?

00:45:37.790 --> 00:45:40.340
And so it was going
to happen anyway.

00:45:40.340 --> 00:45:42.930
And so what Bush did
was he convinced FDR

00:45:42.930 --> 00:45:46.560
that this was something that
we needed to get in front of,

00:45:46.560 --> 00:45:48.410
and who knew how far
along the Germans were,

00:45:48.410 --> 00:45:50.380
because they discovered
the darn thing.

00:45:50.380 --> 00:45:53.130
And so that became
the Manhattan Project.

00:45:53.130 --> 00:45:54.430
But it was something

00:45:54.430 --> 00:45:56.690
that eventually would've
happened anyway.

00:45:56.690 --> 00:46:01.900
So timing, as I noted
earlier, is critical in life.

00:46:01.900 --> 00:46:05.120
Ninety-nine percent of
success is showing up.

00:46:05.120 --> 00:46:07.830
But you've got to be in the
right place at the right time.

