00:47:27.730 --> 00:47:32.630
But many of the -- let's
just say many of the ideas

00:47:32.630 --> 00:47:33.930
that were later developed

00:47:33.930 --> 00:47:39.120
into war devices originated
elsewhere and were brought in.

00:47:39.120 --> 00:47:43.610
We benefitted greatly by the
number of emigres from Germany

00:47:43.610 --> 00:47:46.230
who came over just
prior to World War II.

00:47:46.230 --> 00:47:47.530
They brought their scientific

00:47:47.530 --> 00:47:49.140
and technical knowledge
with them.

00:47:49.140 --> 00:47:52.030
The Brits, the Brits,
when they got --

00:47:52.030 --> 00:47:55.340
when they were getting their
butt handed to them in 1940,

00:47:55.340 --> 00:47:58.190
came over to the United States
and started pushing on us some

00:47:58.190 --> 00:48:01.780
of their laboratory
concepts that had maybe,

00:48:01.780 --> 00:48:03.760
might have been helpful.

00:48:03.760 --> 00:48:05.880
For example, the
klystron, which is the heart

00:48:05.880 --> 00:48:08.400
of not only your
microwave dinner,

00:48:08.400 --> 00:48:10.780
but also the airborne radar.

00:48:10.780 --> 00:48:13.000
They brought over a laboratory
sample and then we had

00:48:13.000 --> 00:48:14.480
to take it and turn it

00:48:14.480 --> 00:48:16.980
into something they could
actually use in an airplane.

00:48:16.980 --> 00:48:20.650
The variable time fuse, the
VT fuse originally started

00:48:20.650 --> 00:48:24.230
out a little bit as an idea
that somebody in the UK had.

00:48:24.230 --> 00:48:25.530
They brought it over.

00:48:25.530 --> 00:48:28.480
We had to turn it into something
that would survive 20,000 Gs

00:48:28.480 --> 00:48:31.260
when fired out of a
cannon and still explode

00:48:31.260 --> 00:48:32.910
at the other end
at the right time.

00:48:32.910 --> 00:48:36.940
So let's just say
we did not have --

00:48:36.940 --> 00:48:40.880
we had not devoted the thought
to developing the groundwork

00:48:40.880 --> 00:48:43.710
for development, but
once we got the ideas,

00:48:43.710 --> 00:48:46.510
we were very successful in
turning them into something

00:48:46.510 --> 00:48:48.600
that made a difference
on the battlefield.

00:48:48.600 --> 00:48:50.900
&gt;&gt; Thank you.

00:48:54.620 --> 00:49:00.200
&gt;&gt; Hi. My question is, a lot of
the devices that you're talking

00:49:00.200 --> 00:49:03.630
about that were developed
in the war period,

00:49:03.630 --> 00:49:07.930
and even in the decades
after, eventually filtered

00:49:07.930 --> 00:49:11.480
out into other civilian uses,

00:49:11.480 --> 00:49:12.960
like you just mentioned
the microwave,

00:49:12.960 --> 00:49:18.620
etc. To what extent is
that still happening,

00:49:18.620 --> 00:49:22.220
and is there a pipeline
between --

00:49:22.220 --> 00:49:25.010
that pipeline between
what's developed

00:49:25.010 --> 00:49:27.430
in these military
research studies

00:49:27.430 --> 00:49:33.070
out into civilian
life and industry?

00:49:33.070 --> 00:49:36.580
&gt;&gt; Daniel Else: Well, I don't
think there's a way to measure,

00:49:36.580 --> 00:49:38.470
let's say, the flow of
the number of ideas.

00:49:38.470 --> 00:49:40.510
But if you take a
look at the funding,

00:49:40.510 --> 00:49:43.230
let's just say the funding,
that goes into research

00:49:43.230 --> 00:49:45.880
and development, on the part
of the federal government,

00:49:45.880 --> 00:49:47.380
particularly the
Department of Defense,

00:49:47.380 --> 00:49:51.360
and let's say private
industry, that line --

00:49:51.360 --> 00:49:54.530
we started the post-war period
with the Department of Defense

00:49:54.530 --> 00:49:57.460
or War and Navy Departments
kind of up here,

00:49:57.460 --> 00:49:59.950
and commercial entities
down here,

00:49:59.950 --> 00:50:02.920
and that line crossed
in the early 1950s.

00:50:02.920 --> 00:50:05.500
And it looks like this now.

00:50:05.500 --> 00:50:08.360
So that's why you see,
that's why you see soldiers

00:50:08.360 --> 00:50:10.610
out in the field using
their smartphones:

00:50:10.610 --> 00:50:11.910
because they're smarter

00:50:11.910 --> 00:50:13.760
than anything DoD can
give them and such.

00:50:13.760 --> 00:50:17.670
And there are, though -- DoD
has been conscious of that,

00:50:17.670 --> 00:50:20.300
and over the recent
years, let's say,

00:50:20.300 --> 00:50:25.120
they've been trying very
hard to build pathways

00:50:25.120 --> 00:50:30.020
to bring commercial
technology back into the defense

00:50:30.020 --> 00:50:34.530
and create pathways such
that that can happen quickly,

00:50:34.530 --> 00:50:36.980
expeditiously and,
hopefully, cheaply.

00:50:36.980 --> 00:50:38.280
And in fact, there's a member

