of a bunch of rapid acquisition
pathways, prototyping funds

00:51:22.690 --> 00:51:24.420
that they should carry forward

00:51:24.420 --> 00:51:27.000
to have those efforts be a
little bit less fragmented

00:51:27.000 --> 00:51:30.730
and a little bit
more successful?

00:51:30.730 --> 00:51:32.030
&gt;&gt; Daniel Else: Hmm.

00:51:32.030 --> 00:51:33.560
Well, trying to make it
less fragmented implies

00:51:33.560 --> 00:51:35.480
that you need a central
organization that's actually

00:51:35.480 --> 00:51:36.780
governing it.

00:51:36.780 --> 00:51:38.880
And as we just -- you just
saw a sampling of the number

00:51:38.880 --> 00:51:40.810
of organizations in
the Department --

00:51:40.810 --> 00:51:42.730
just within the Department
of Defense that are devoted

00:51:42.730 --> 00:51:45.940
to research and engineering,
and so therefore,

00:51:45.940 --> 00:51:50.800
I think until you get a
strong, centralized authority

00:51:50.800 --> 00:51:52.310
within the department,
